    <div class="main">
      <div class="title">Operational Rules</div>

      <div class="container">
	<h1 id="list">List of Skills</h1>
        <p>
          Where multiple scalable dimensions are given, a certain
          skill level only applies to one, i.e. of multiple dimensions
          shall be increased, multiple skill levels must be available.
        </p>
        <p>
          Specialties apply, in particular at higher levels, for each
          skill.
        </p>
	<h3 id="trfi">Track &#038; Field</h3>
        <p>
          Each column is a separate skill.
        </p>
	<table>
          <caption>Table 1</caption>
 	  <tr>
            <th>Level</th>
            <th>Run (10s)</th>
            <th>Level Jump (2s)</th>
            <th>Endurance</th>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
            <td>0</td><td>5 m/s</td>
            <td>2 m</td><td>-0.1 Stufe / s</td>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
            <td>10</td><td>7 m/s</td>
            <td>2.8 m</td><td>-0.03 Stufe / s</td>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
            <td>20</td><td>10 m/s</td>
            <td>4 m</td><td>-0.01 Stufe / s</td>
	  </tr>
	</table>
