	<h3 id="plant">Plants</h3>
	<p>
	  The <em>Effect classes</em> are split into <em>pain
	  suppressant, blood clot, ...</em> for healing, for poisons
	  they are <em>nerve poison, inducing stomache colics,
	  ...</em>.  Columns represent separate dimensions.
	</p>
	<table class="c5">
          <caption>Table 3</caption>
	  <tr>
            <th>Level</th>
            <th>Local Species</th>
            <th>Foreign Species</th>
            <th>Effect Classes</th>
            <th>Location</th>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
            <td>0</td><td>30%</td><td>0%</td><td>2</td><td>Humans</td>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
            <td>10</td><td>60%</td><td>20%</td><td>4</td><td>Domestic Animals</td>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
            <td>20</td><td>90%</td><td>40%</td><td>8</td><td>Local Species</td>
	  </tr>
	</table>
	<h3 id="animal">Animals</h3>
	<p>
	  The <em>Effect classes</em> are split into use classes
	  <em>milk, wool, ...</em> and danger classes <em>physically
	  superior, aggressive, poison bite, devours wooden building,
	  ...</em>.  Columns represent separate dimensions.
	</p>
	<table>
          <caption>Table 4</caption>
	  <tr>
            <th>Level</th>
            <th>Local Species</th>
            <th>Foreign Species</th>
            <th>Effect Classes</th>
	  </tr>
