	  </tr>
	  <tr>
            <td>10</td><td>60%</td><td>20%</td><td>4</td>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
            <td>20</td><td>90%</td><td>40%</td><td>8</td>
	  </tr>
	</table>
	<h3 id="med">Medicine</h3>
	<p>
	  Diagnostic classes are split into hazard classes
	  <em>contagious, may have complications, ...</em> and healing
	  classes <em>needs rest, ointments, splints, ...</em>.  Since
	  diseases and wounds come in many forms, we abstract here and
	  only provide a bonus to self-healing in <em>therapy</em>.
	  Columns represent separate dimensions.
	</p>
	<table class="c3">
          <caption>Table 5</caption>
	  <tr>
